2794 . a mhac :
Rev . Allan MacQueen , son of the foregoing , who was admitted as minister of the parish of North Uist on the day on which the lines were composed . He was born in 1742 , and was educated at King ’ s College , Aberdeen , where he graduated M . A . on 2nd April 1764 . He was licensed by the Presbytery of Uist on 9th December 1768 , and ordained missionary in Benbecula on 29th March 1769 . Next year he became minister of the parish of North Uist , as already mentioned , having been presented by George III in August . He married Mary , daughter of William MacDonald of Vallay , with issue , a daughter , Mary , born 19th December 1783 ( subject of the song Màiri Bhòidheach by Alexander Stewart ) , and a son , Donald , captain in the Royal Scots , born 23rd December 1784 . Rev . John Lanne Buchanan describes Mr MacQueen as follows : “ Another valuable farm in North Uist is possessed by the reverend gentleman of Ty - Geary [Tigh a ’ Gheàrraidh] ;
who of all the tacksmen , clergymen , and gentlemen of the Western Isles of Scotland , is the largest and jolliest as well as one of the most hospitable and best natured .

